  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of international and national regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here are key aspects of this framework:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) in the United States\n- Money Laundering Control Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Comprehensive regulations for financial institutions\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n\n4. Legal Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n5. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Regular audits\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Staff training programs\n- Internal control systems\n- Reporting mechanisms\n\n6. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between jurisdictions\n- Cross-border investigation protocols\n- Extradition agreements\n\nThis framework aims to prevent financial crimes and ensure transparency in financial transactions.",
